LAGOS – A Lagos State Special Offenc­es Court was, on Wednesday, told by Mr. Sunday Ubani, a prosecution witness of the Special Anti-Fraud Unit, Mil­verton, Ikoyi, Lagos, how Mo­bil Plc received only 3444met­ric tonnes from alleged stolen 10,000 metric tonnes of its valid contract with Nadabo Energy Limited. He made the disclosure while being led evidence by Rotimi Jacobs (SAN) in a suit marked ID/7980c/2018 before Justice Mojisola Dada. The marketers, Yusuf Kwande and Osahon Ase­mota are facing three-count criminal charges alongside five companies: Trafigura Behee BV, Trafigura PTE Limited, Mettle Energy and Gas, Rembrandt Limited and Jil Engineering and Oil Ser­vices Limited. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The charge is bordering on conspiracy, stealing and receiving stolen property. He told the court that in­vestigation conducted by his team uncovered that Nadabo Energy Limited entered into an agreement with the Mobil Plc for the supply of 10,000 metric tonnes of Automotive Gas Oil. Bishop Of Awka Charges FG On Diversification Yuletide: Gov. Ugwuanyi Prays For Divine Intervention He said Nadabo Energy invited Mettle Energy to exe­cute the contract on its behalf with a fund raised by Nadabo from Spring Bank as consign­ee of supplied product from Trafigura. He said upon an investi­gation of the allegation that the product was off-spec and contaminated was a tissue of lies, as Department of Petro­leum Regulations and Q&Q at different times confirmed that the supplied product met the required standard. “There was an agreement between Nadabo Energy and Mobil. At Mobil, we met Charles. He sent one CSO and others to accompany us inside. “Mobil confirmed that they have a contract for the supply of 10,000 metric tonnes AGO with Nadabo. They informed us that they received 3,444 metric tonnes from the total contract. Whatever product supplied to Mobil, they pay according to the contract terms,” Ubani said. He told the court that the vessel which conveyed the product carried 25,000 metric tonnes of AGO out of which 10,000 metric tonnes was dis­charged for Mobil/Nadabo Energy Limited contract. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION